originalText.text:
Absolutely awful experience here. We made a reservation on SpotHero for marathon Sunday as we needed a close place to park near the end of the race. We planned ahead and did all the right things. I arrived right as my reservation began and the attendants turned me away - told me to leave even after showing my confirmed and paid for reservation.

They were so rude and mean to me they I actually began crying as my entire days plans almost changed - I had three young children in the car with me and planned in advance.  The worst part is spot hero still won’t refund me.

A terrible experience and couldn’t believe how mean and insensitive people could be.

originalText.text: Horrible service.  My family and I were visiting the Museum of Natural History and I used the Spot Hero app for a reservation. When we returned the attendant was yelling in Spanish that he hates people with reservations and that people who use the app are the cheapest people in the world.  He may have thought I didn’t speak Spanish but nonetheless if you don’t like the application then don’t use it and I’ll give my business elsewhere. The attendant also banged the door of another vehicle as he ranted repeating that he hates reservations and that my family and I were cheap.  This made a wonderful day at the museum end on a sour note.  Do not park here.

originalText.text: Horrible place stay away!! Me GF and I were going out and we parked here, her Tucson, me a smart car. She paid 25, I was charged 65. The guy didn’t tell me it was going to be 65 till I had been there 3hrs. $20 on the weekend. The sign is so misleading wiki that the price and even as an irate customer he still charged me $65. This was smiths worst experience in parking in my life in this city and by far the most expensive 3hrs I have ever paid for. I don’t even make close to that. Horrible place stay away

originalText.text: Parked here today, full day, then I made the FATAL mistake of asking for a receipt- I saw the receipt was for a different car, so I questioned it (mostly to make sure the attendant was going to bring the right car)- the attendant snapped “All you need it for is the amount, don’t you?” (actually, I would need to have the right car listed, especially a company car, but that’s beside the point). He then slammed the door to the office and got my car, then when he got out he snidely remarked “That’s the last time I do a favor for you!”
